    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-27T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-27T01:00:00-05:00" n="601"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-27T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 27, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Delam 32. For the President and Acting Secretary from the Secretary. If you have
                    approved the text of the Four Nation Declaration (reference Delam No. 31<note
                        n="97" xml:id="d601fn97">October 26, 1943, <ref
                            target="frus1943China#pg_829">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, China, p.
                        829</ref>.</note>) as adopted in the Conference yesterday, I would
                    appreciate receiving immediately your authorization to sign this Declaration on
                    behalf of the United States. It is of vital importance <pb facs="0655" n="645"
                        xml:id="pg_645"/> that I have these powers at the earliest possible
                        moment.<note n="98" xml:id="d601fn98">The Acting Secretary replied in Amdel
                        No. 52 (telegram No. 1102), October 27, 1943, 10 a.m.: “Personal for
                        Secretary Hull. This is to confirm my statement over the telephone to Mr.
                        Gray that the President has authorized you to sign the Four Nation
                        Declaration as modified in the light of your telegrams from Moscow.”
                        (740.0011 Moscow/69a)</note> [Hull.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
